The paper deals with the analysis of boolean conjunctive normal forms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of autarkies and minimally unsatisfiable clause-sets suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of variables and their occurrences suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the analysis of the minimal variable-degree and the surplus suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
